2 Read the data

Use OSD 2014-2015 LGC 99%

dataset_map <- c(2)
df.metabarcode_genus_color <- read.delim("Pelago genus colors metabarcodes.txt")

Metabarcode database reading

# Connect to metabarcodes database
db_metabarcodes <- dbConnect(MySQL(), user = "root", password = "root", dbname = "metabarcodes", 
    host = "localhost")

# Read database tables and filters according to taxonomy and type of samples

otus <- dbGetQuery(db_metabarcodes, "select * from otus")
otus_select <- otus %>% filter(str_detect(class, "Pelago"))

samples <- dbGetQuery(db_metabarcodes, "select * from samples")
samples_select <- samples %>% filter(dataset_id %in% dataset_map) %>% filter(depth_level == 
    "surface") %>% filter(DNA_RNA == "DNA") %>% filter(year == 2014)

read_abundance <- dbGetQuery(db_metabarcodes, "select * from read_abundance")

# Disonnect from metabarcodes database
dbDisconnect(db_metabarcodes)
[1] TRUE
# Joins the tables otu and read abundance
otus_select <- inner_join(read_abundance, otus_select)

# Only keep samples that have been selected
otus_select <- otus_select %>% filter((dataset_id %in% samples_select$dataset_id) & 
    (sample_code %in% samples_select$sample_code))

3 Summarizing data

# Summarize per genus at each station
sample_genus <- otus_select %>% group_by(dataset_id, sample_code, genus) %>% 
    summarize(reads_total_genus = sum(read_number))

# Spread with one column per genus
sample_genus_wide <- sample_genus %>% ungroup() %>% spread(key = genus, value = reads_total_genus) %>% 
    right_join(select(samples_select, dataset_id, sample_code))

sample_genus_wide[is.na(sample_genus_wide)] <- 0

# Summarize per overall by genus
total_genus <- sample_genus %>% group_by(genus) %>% summarize(reads_total_genus_overall = sum(reads_total_genus))

# Total Pelago at each station
sample_class <- sample_genus %>% group_by(dataset_id, sample_code) %>% summarize(reads_total_class = sum(reads_total_genus))

# Reads Dominant genus at each station and remove duplicate
sample_genus_dominant <- sample_genus %>% group_by(dataset_id, sample_code) %>% 
    top_n(1, reads_total_genus) %>% distinct(dataset_id, sample_code, .keep_all = TRUE) %>% 
    rename(genus_dominant = genus, reads_total_genus_dominant = reads_total_genus)

# Assemble everything in the big table
metabarcodes_genus <- samples_select %>% left_join(sample_class) %>% left_join(sample_genus_dominant) %>% 
    mutate(reads_total_class_pct = reads_total_class/reads_total * 100) %>% 
    left_join(sample_genus_wide)
metabarcodes_genus$reads_total_class_pct[is.na(metabarcodes_genus$reads_total_class_pct)] <- 0

write.table(metabarcodes_genus, "Metabarcodes_Pelago.txt", quote = FALSE, sep = "\t", 
    na = "", row.names = FALSE)

6 Define colors and background map

# Define constants for the map
size_points <- 2.5
size_cross <- 1
scaling_factor <- 30
color_ice <- "lightslateblue"
color_water <- "red"
color_cultures <- "green"
color_not_present <- "blue"
color_continents <- "grey80"

# Get the world map for the rworldmap package
worldMap <- getMap(resolution = "coarse")  # Change to 'coarse' for global maps / 'low' for regional maps
world.points <- fortify(worldMap)
world.points$region <- world.points$id
world.df <- world.points[, c("long", "lat", "group", "region")]

# Background map using the maps package world.df <- map_data('world')

background_map <- ggplot() + geom_polygon(data = world.df, aes(x = long, y = lat, 
    group = group, fill = "")) + scale_fill_manual(values = color_continents, 
    guide = FALSE) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = (-4:4) * 45) + scale_y_continuous(breaks = (-2:2) * 
    30) + xlab("Longitude") + ylab("Latitude") + coord_fixed(1.3) + theme_bw()
# species_map <- species_map + coord_map () # Mercator projection
# species_map <- species_map + coord_map('gilbert') # Nice for the poles

8 Maps for each metabarcode group at species level

Only consider stations where more than 10 reads of Pelago Only consider genera that have more than 50 reads total

map_array <- list()  # to store the maps to do tiled graph
map_array_europe <- list()

total_genus_map <- total_genus %>% filter(reads_total_genus_overall > 50)

for (one_genus in total_genus_map$genus) {
    
    df_map <- metabarcodes_genus %>% mutate_(read_my_genus = one_genus) %>% 
        dplyr::filter((read_my_genus == 0) | (reads_total_class < 10))
    
    genus_title <- str_replace_all(one_genus, "_", " ")
    genus_title <- str_replace_all(genus_title, " sp.", "")
    
    one_genus_map <- background_map + geom_point(data = df_map, aes(x = longitude, 
        y = latitude), color = color_not_present, size = size_cross, shape = 3) + 
        ggtitle(genus_title)
    
    if (str_detect(genus_title, "Tri")) {
        one_genus_map <- one_genus_map + theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "italic"))
    }
    
    df_map <- metabarcodes_genus %>% mutate_(read_my_genus = one_genus) %>% 
        dplyr::filter((read_my_genus > 0) & (reads_total_class >= 10))
    
    one_genus_map <- one_genus_map + geom_point(data = df_map, aes(x = longitude, 
        y = latitude, size = read_my_genus/reads_total_class * 100), color = color_water) + 
        theme(legend.position = "top") + guides(color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 5))) + 
        scale_size("% of Pelago barcodes", range = c(0, 5), limits = c(0, 100), 
            breaks = c(10, 25, 50, 100))
    # range gives maximum and minimum size of symbols, limits the extent of the
    # scale replace guide = 'legend' by guide=FALSE to remove the legend....
    
    print(one_genus_map)
    
    map_array[[one_genus]] <- one_genus_map
    
    # Zoom on Europe
    
    one_genus_map_europe <- one_genus_map + coord_map("mercator", xlim = c(-30, 
        60), ylim = c(30, 60)) + scale_x_continuous(breaks = (-3:6) * 10) + 
        scale_y_continuous(breaks = (6:12) * 5)
    
    print(one_genus_map_europe)
    
    map_array_europe[[one_genus]] <- one_genus_map_europe
    
}

grid_map <- grid.arrange(grobs = map_array, ncol = 3, nrow = 3, clip = FALSE)

ggsave(plot = grid_map, filename = paste("Fig Pelago maps barcodes 2.0.pdf", 
    sep = ""), width = 25, height = 20, scale = 1.5, units = "cm", useDingbats = FALSE)

grid_map_europe <- grid.arrange(grobs = map_array_europe, ncol = 3, nrow = 3, 
    clip = FALSE)

ggsave(plot = grid_map_europe, filename = paste("Fig Pelago maps barcodes Europe 2.0.pdf", 
    sep = ""), width = 25, height = 20, scale = 1.2, units = "cm", useDingbats = FALSE)
